  "theoryOfChange": "UNICEF USA's Impact Fund for Children has co-developed a 'Child-Lens Investment Framework' which serves as a roadmap for investors to frame strategies and direct capital toward advancing child outcomes and minimizing child harm. This framework includes core principles, a case for investment, an analysis of the global market landscape, and a description of the Child-Lens Investment ecosystem. It also provides a toolkit with resources, a Due Diligence Questionnaire, and a Child-Lens Metrics Bank to assist investors in implementing this approach. The Impact Fund reports impact through two frameworks: an Input/Output/Outcomes Framework and by mapping to Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). The broader UNICEF organization also utilizes a 'Theory of Change' within its Strategic Plans, such as the UNICEF Strategic Plan, 2022\u20132025, which outlines programmatic goals, result areas, change strategies, and enablers.",
